My wife and I were looking for a little late bite. We were walking around and we have passed SoHo before. We decided to give it a shot.  Our server was nice and did a good job. We decided to try there house made waffle dessert with ice cream and chocolate syrup. We also ordered a bottle of Rose wine from there special list ( Oh yea..High end stuff!!). The dessert was decent overall. The waffle was a bit dense but I couldnt tell for sure if it was truly made from scratch. The ice cream was standard vanilla ice cream. The wine was good though and we enjoyed it. The Menu was very limited due to the COVID so that was understandable.  Overall, this was a nice place to eat. Its trying to be a bit 'overly trendy' in my opinion with the food.  It didnt highly impress me overall but it was still enjoyable to eat here.

We made it to Soho for brunch on a Sunday to try something new. It was cute with inside and outside seating options, something for everyone on the menu and generous refillable alcoholic brunch drink options.  We had the house made chicken and waffle, side of bacon and steak and eggs. Everything was made in house and tasty. The portions were a good size, filling and a decent price. It was nice to see small portions of fried potatoes and fruit on the plates to have some variety without having to order additional sides. The potatoes were super crispy and delish!  There were drink options that were a little more deluxe on the menu. We opted for the $10 pitchers of mimosa and bloody Mary’s for our group. Perfect for a relaxing Sunday afternoon.  The staff was wearing masks and following covid protocols when we were there. We felt safe and enjoyed our brunch.

My wife and I have been coming to Soho Burger Bar since they opened the restaurant and we love the changes they've made.  Everything we've had has been fresh and flavorful from the salads to the burgers.  I have tried every item on the menu and have enjoyed them all!  My wife loves the Steak & Egg burger and the Tuna Burger.  Try the spiked shakes - the Kentucky Caramel is  amazing!  If you have room for dessert try the homemade ice cream sandwiches or the hot fudge chocolate caramel brownie sundae.  You won't be disappointed.

My hubby and I stopped in for Restaurant Week.  I had the Steak and Eggs Burger and enjoyed every bite.  I am not one who normally goes for a meal that sounds like it might be "messy".  I am so glad I tried it.  It was juicy and flavorful.  I liked it so much that I am going back for another one this week - which is rare for me. My hubby loved the truffle tater tots.  We each had a mini chocolate chip ice cream sandwich for dessert and they were scrumptious.  The portion was perfect - just enough to satisfy your sweet tooth, but not so much that you feel guilty splurging on dessert.  And the owner's mom makes the cookies (and other desserts) - just like Mama!  The restaurant/bar itself has a good vibe to it.  Sports games on the large screen tvs and trendy music all around.  The staff is warm and welcoming - and the service was excellent.  I highly recommend it.

I don't know why everyone complains about this place, I am convinced that the only people that leave reviews are ones that just feel like complaining. Jack the bartender is personable and knows how to make drinks. The comments about being understaffed are ridiculous, every time I go in there the place is overstaffed and the servers continually check on your table. The burgers are incredible, they offer gourmet options that are cooked perfectly and build your own burgers. The only criticism is how dark it is inside, but I'm over it. Overall, this is a great place to eat.

One of the most horrific bars I have seen in a while!!!! I'm from Toronto, so I know what a good bar should be like. This is one of the bars you'll see on bar rescue in the next few years, if it survives till then. They say it's one of the better bars in Buffalo, but if that's true I'd hate to see the other ones. Servers don't know which way is up and down in there. They under pour, then take shots themselves when they feel like. They are slow and each server only knows how to pour 2 to 3 drinks total. You ask for a rum and coke and they get confused. The bar was understaffed or at least seemed that way, cause the staff spent more time socializing then working. I also noticed the bars cleanliness, which I have to say is a total joke. I’d never advise drinking from one of those glasses.   I’d avoid this place at all costs!!!!!
